def quantile(self, q=0.5, axis=0, numeric_only=True, interpolation="linear"):
    self._check_percentile(q)
    
    # Get the numeric data if numeric_only is True, otherwise use self
    data = self._get_numeric_data() if numeric_only else self

    # Get the axis number based on the input
    axis = self._get_axis_number(axis)

    # Transpose the data if the axis is column-wise
    is_transposed = axis == 1
    if is_transposed:
        data = data.T

    # Compute the quantile based on the provided parameters
    result = data.quantile(q=q, axis=axis, interpolation=interpolation)

    # If the result is a 2D array, create a new DataFrame; otherwise, create a Series
    if result.ndim == 2:
        result = self._constructor(result)
    else:
        result = self._constructor_sliced(result, name=q)

    # Transpose the result back if the data was transposed
    if is_transposed:
        result = result.T

    return result
